name: agricultural ecosystem
synonyms: agricultural environment, agrarian, farmed land, horticultural, agroecosystem
definition: An ecosystem managed with a purpose, usually to produce crops or animal products.

name: agricultural terrace
definition: A piece of sloped plane that has been cut into a series of successively receding flat surfaces or platforms, which resemble steps, for the purposes of more effective farming.

name: alpine biome
synonyms: alpine region, alpine zone, alpine environment, alpine ecosystem
definition: A biome which is subject to alpine altitudinal conditions.

name: alpine tree line ecotone
definition: A tree line ecotone across which trees cease to grow due to the low temperatures or duration of snow cover that occur at increased elevations above mean sea level.

name: alpine tundra biome
definition: A tundra biome which exists at high altitudes and where vegetation - dominated by a few species of dwarf shrubs, a few grasses, sedges, lichens, and mosses - is stunted due to low temperatures and high winds.

name: alpine tundra ecosystem
definition: A tundra ecosystem which exists at high altitudes and where vegetation is stunted due to low temperatures and high winds.

name: anthropogenic terrestrial biome
synonyms: anthropogenic biome, anthromes, human biomes, intensive land-use biome
definition: An anthropogenic terrestrial biome is a terrestrial biome which has community structures determined by human activity.

name: apiary
definition: An apiary is a place where beehives of honey bees are kept and maintained by beekeepers.

name: aquatic biome
synonyms: lives in water, lives on water
definition: A biome which is determined by a water body and which has ecological climax communities adapted to life in or on water.

name: aquatic ecosystem
synonyms: lives in water, lives on water
definition: An ecosystem in a body of water.

name: arid biome
definition: A biome which is subject to arid environmental conditions.

name: banana plantation
definition: A commercial agricultural facility found in tropical climates where bananas are grown.

name: broadleaf forest
synonyms: broad-leaved tree, broad-leaf tree, broadleaf tree, deciduous forest, deciduous forests
definition: A forest biome which contains densely packed populations or communities of broadleaf trees, strongly limiting light penetration to the forest floor.

name: cloud forest
synonyms: water forest, primas forest, tropical montane cloud forest, moist forest
definition: A montane forest ecosystem which 1) is evergreen, 2) present on mountains where there is frequent cloud and mist cover, 3) which has a large proportion of ferns and mosses in its plant communities, growing on all tree trunks and branches present in the ecosystem, and 3) harvests aerosolised water and adds it to the terrestrial water supply.

name: coastal wetland ecosystem
definition: A wetland ecosystem which overlaps both terrestrial and marine ecosystems.

name: coconut plantation
definition: A commercial agricultural facility found in tropical climates where coconuts are grown.

name: coffee plantation
definition: A commercial agricultural facility found in tropical climates where coffee is grown.

name: concentration basin mediterranean sea biome
definition: The concentration basin mediterranean sea biome comprises expressions of the mediterranean sea biome that have higher salinity than bordering oceans due to evaporation. Water exchange consists of inflow of the fresher oceanic water in the upper layer and outflow of the saltier mediterranean water in the lower layer of the connecting channel.

name: conifer woodland
definition: A conifer woodland is a woodland which has a tree community primarily composed of coniferous trees, from the Division Pinophyta, also known as Coniferophyta or Coniferae.

name: coniferous forest biome
definition: A coniferous forest biome is a forest biome which contains densely packed populations or communities of coniferous trees, strongly limiting light penetration to the forest floor.

name: cotton plantation
definition: A commercial agricultural facility found in tropical climates where cotton is grown.

name: cropland biome
definition: A cropland ecosystem in which dominant ecological communities are maintained in a stable state - mimicking a climax community - by human intervention.

name: cropland ecosystem
definition: An ecosystem which 1) is determined by communities of annual crops, perennial woody crops, or by actively tilled land, 2) is primarily used for agricultural activity, and 3) contains no village or larger human settlement.

name: cypress swamp
definition: A cypress swamp is a swamp which has a plant community dominated by Cupressaceae, often swamp cypresses. Swamp cypresses typically belong to the genus Taxodium or the species Glyptostrobus pensilis and Actinostrobus pyramidalis.

name: dense settlement biome
synonyms: urban environment, urban area, built-up area
definition: A dense settlement biome is an anthropogenic terrestrial biome which is primarily used for human habitation, recreation, and industry within built structures with little other land use.

name: desert biome
synonyms: deserts, barren land, dry environment, dry climate, low precipitation
definition: A desert biome is a terrestrial biome which loses more liquid water by evapotranspiration than is supplied by precipitation and includes communities adapted to these conditions.

name: desert ecosystem
synonyms: deserts, barren land, dry environment, dry climate, low precipitation
definition: An ecosystem in which the composition, structure, and function of resident ecological assemblages are primarily determined by a desert.

name: desert tree line ecotone
definition: A tree line ecotone across which trees cease to grow due to insufficient water availability due to a lack of water-based precipitation.

name: digestive tract environment
synonyms: lives in digestive tract, lives in gut
definition: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by a digestive tract.

name: disturbed ecosystem
synonyms: disturbed environment, perturbed ecosystem, perturbed environment
definition: An ecosystem which has been subject to a perturbation, that is, the ecosystem has undergone a pronounced change in response to a change in environmental conditions or other perturbation.

name: dry woodland
definition: A dry woodland is a woodland which occurs in areas of rain shadow in a tropical marine climate,  receives very little rainfall,  typically has rapidly draining soils and trees which have adaptations to dry climates such as thick bark, small leaves, and the disposition to shed their leaves.

name: ecological corridor
synonyms: wildlife corridor, habitat corridor, green corridor
definition: An ecosystem which bridges two or more adjoining ecosystems and through which organisms may move or propagate.

name: environment associated with a fungal tissue
synonyms: lives on fungi, lives in fungi
definition: An environmental system determined by part of a living or dead fungus.

name: environment associated with a plant part or small plant
synonyms: lives on plants, lives in plants
definition: An environmental system determined by part of a living or dead plant, or a whole small plant.

name: estuarine biome
definition: Expressions of the estuarine biome occur at wide lower courses of a rivers where they flow into a sea. Estuaries experience tidal flows and their water is a changing mixture of fresh and salt.

name: face skin environment
synonyms: facial skin, face hairs, face hair follicles
definition: Environment on or in skin of the face, e.g. hair follicles

name: farm
definition: An area of land which is used for the cultivation of crops or grazing of livestock, including any agricultural constructions therein.

name: feather environment
definition: A branching, hair-like structure that grows on the bodies of birds, used for flight, swimming, protection and display.

name: feed storage space
synonyms: stored product, feed store, feed storage, grain store, fodder
definition: A physical space, which may or may not be in a construction, which is used to store animal feed for agricultural purposes.

name: feedlot
definition: A feedlot is a plot of land on which livestock are fattened for market

name: fen
definition: A freshwater peat land with chemically basic (which roughly means alkaline) ground water.

name: fish farm
synonyms: pisciculture, aquaculture, fish hatchery, carp farm, salmon farm, tilapia farm, trout farm, bream farm
definition: A facility in which fish are raised commercially in tanks or enclosures, usually for food.

name: flood meadow ecosystem
synonyms: flood-meadow, floodmeadow, flood meadows, flood-meadows, floodmeadows
definition: An area of grassland or pasture beside a river, subject to seasonal flooding.

name: flooded grassland
synonyms: flooded grasslands, flooded savanna, flooded savannas
definition: Large expanses or complexes of flooded grasslands

name: flooded grassland biome
synonyms: flooded grasslands, flooded savanna, flooded savannas
definition: Large expanses or complexes of flooded grasslands

name: flooded savanna biome
synonyms: flooded grasslands, flooded savanna, flooded savannas
definition: A flooded savanna biome is a savanna biome which has very wet to saturated soil moisture content.

name: forest biome
definition: A forest ecosystem in which dominant ecological communities have reached their climax successional state.

name: forest ecosystem
definition: An ecosystem which is determined by communities of plants with a tree growth form and in which members of those communities form continuous or discontinuous regions of canopy cover.

name: freshwater biome
definition: An aquatic biome which is determined by a body of freshwater.

name: freshwater ecosystem
definition: An aquatic biome which is determined by a body of freshwater.

name: freshwater lake biome
synonyms: fresh water lake, freshwater lake, freshwater lakes
definition: A biome which is determined by a freshwater lake.

name: freshwater marsh
synonyms: fresh water marsh, freshwater marshes, freshwater swamp
definition: A marsh in which soils are saturated with water that contains low concentrations of salts.

name: freshwater river biome
synonyms: fresh water river, freshwater rivers, freshwater stream, river, stream, rivers, streams
definition: A large and often winding stream which drains a land mass, carrying water down from higher areas to a lower point, oftentimes ending in another body of water.

name: freshwater wetland ecosystem
synonyms: fresh water wetland, freshwater wetlands, freshwater swamp
definition: A wetland which is inundated with water that contains low concentrations of salts.

name: grassland biome
definition: A grassland ecosystem in which dominant ecological communities have reached their climax successional state.

name: grassland ecosystem
definition: An ecosystem in which grasses (Graminae) are the dominant form of vegetation and determine the system's structure and dynamics.

name: intermittent wetland
synonyms: temporary wetland, temporary wetlands, seasonal wetland, seasonal wetlands
definition: A wetland ecosystem which is sometimes inundated or saturated by surface or ground water sufficient to support, and that under normal circumstances do support, a prevalence of vegetation typically adapted for life in saturated soil conditions.

name: intertidal ecosystem
definition: An ecosystem which overlaps those areas of the foreshore and seabed that are exposed to the air at low tide and submerged at high tide.

name: intestine environment
synonyms: lives in digestive tract, lives in gut, lives in intestines
definition: An environmental system determined by an intestine.

name: juniper woodland
definition: A juniper woodland is a woodland which has a tree community primarily composed of trees of the genus Juniperus.

name: lacustrine mudflat
definition: A wetland that forms when mud is deposited by a stream.

name: large river biome
synonyms: large river, large rivers, river, rivers
definition: A large and often winding water body which drains a land mass, carrying water down from higher areas to a lower point, oftentimes ending in another body of water.

name: large river delta biome
definition: A landform created by deposition of sediment that is carried by a river as the flow leaves its mouth

name: large river headwater biome
definition: The headwaters of a river or stream is the farthest place in that river or stream from its estuary or downstream confluence with another river, as measured along the course of the river. It is also known as a river's source.

name: mangrove biome
definition: A mangrove biome is a terrestrial biome which includes, across its spatial extent, mangrove plants (Rhizophoraceae). Mangrove plants are able to withstand high levels of salinity as well as regions of anoxia and frequent tidal inundation. Mangrove biomes often occur near tropical and sub-tropical estuaries and depositional marine coastal environments where fine sediments (often with high organic content) collect in areas protected from high energy wave action.

name: mangrove swamp
definition: A swamp which is located in tropical or subtropical environments and is determined by communities of trees and shrubs growing saline coastal environments.

name: manure storage space
synonyms: organic fertilizer store, manure store, animal manure
definition: A physical space, which may or may not be in a construction, which is used to store animal manure for agricultural purposes.

name: marine abyssal zone biome
definition: The marine abyssal zone biome comprises regions of the marine benthic biome  between approximately 2500 m and 6000 m depth. This zone generally coincides with the continental rise and the abyssal plain.

name: marine basaltic hydrothermal vent biome
synonyms: hydrothermal vent, hydrothermal vents, black smokers, white smokers, deep sea vent, deep sea vents, basalt vent
definition: A marine basaltic hydrothermal vent biome comprises regions of the marine hydrothermal vent biome hosted on basaltic rocks. Basalt generally has a composition of 45 to 55 wt % SiO2, 2 to 6 wt % total alkalis, 0.5 to 2.0 wt % TiO2, 5 to 14 wt % FeO and 14 wt % or more Al2O3. Contents of CaO are commonly near 10 wt %, those of MgO commonly in the range 5 to 12 wt %.

name: marine bathyal zone biome
synonyms: bathyal zone, bathypelagic, bathypelagic zone, midnight zone
definition: The marine bathyal zone biome comprises regions of the marine benthic biome between approximately 200 m and 3000 m depth. This zone generally coincides with the continental slope.

name: marine benthic biome
synonyms: sea bottom, ocean bottom, benthic zone, bottom of the sea, bottom of the ocean, seabed, seafloor
definition: The marine benthic biome (benthic meaning 'bottom') encompasses the seafloor and includes such areas as shores, littoral or intertidal areas, marine coral reefs, and the deep seabed.

name: marine biome
synonyms: oceanic, pelagic, marine environment, marine ecosystem, sea, ocean
definition: An aquatic biome which is determined by a marine water body, of or pertaining to the sea or ocean.

name: marine black smoker biome
synonyms: black smoker, hydrothermal vent, black smokers, deep sea vent, deep sea vents
definition: A marine black smoker biome comprises regions of the marine hydrothermal vent biome characterised by a black vent plume. This black plume is a consequence of dissolved metals and minerals forming complexes with sulphide and indicates polymetallic sulphide mineral deposits beneath the surface.

name: marine cold seep biome
synonyms: cold seep, cold vent, cold vents, brine pool seepage, deep sea seepage, brine pools
definition: A marine benthic biome which is determined by a cold seep.

name: marine coral reef biome
synonyms: coral reef, coral reefs, reef-building corals
definition: The marine coral reef biome comprises constructional wave-resistant entities which are primarily built by corals and are often cemented together. The growth of these structures is aided by zooxanthellae, algae that are symbiotic with the reef-building corals.

name: marine ecosystem
synonyms: oceanic, pelagic, marine environment, marine ecosystem, sea, ocean
definition: An aquatic ecosystem which is determined by a marine water body, of or pertaining to the sea or ocean.

name: marine hadal zone biome
definition: The marine hadal zone biome describes sea floor deeper than 6000 m such as that of the oceanic trenches.

name: marine hydrothermal vent biome
synonyms: hydrothermal vent, hydrothermal vents, black smokers, white smokers, deep sea vent, deep sea vents, basalt vent
definition: The marine hydrothermal vent biome comprises regions of the marine benthic biome where heat generated due to tectonic activity, either at divergent plate boundaries or convergent ocean plates where back-arc spreading occurs, is released or 'vented' to the surface. The resultant high temperature water jets are laden with dissolved metals and minerals.

name: marine neritic benthic zone biome
synonyms: neritic zone, coastal waters, coastal ocean, sublittoral zone
definition: The marine neritic zone biome comprises sea floor from the high tide mark to a continental shelf break. This zone generally extends to 200 m below average sea level.

name: marine pelagic biome
synonyms: pelagic zone, ocean water column, pelagic, open sea, open ocean
definition: The marine pelagic biome (pelagic meaning open sea) is that of the marine water column, from the surface to the greatest depths.

name: marine reef biome
definition: A biome expressed by strips or ridges of rocks, sand, or coral that rises to or near the surface of a body of marine water.

name: marine salt marsh biome
synonyms: salt marsh, salty marsh, saltmarsh, coastal salt marsh, tidal marsh
definition: The marine salt marsh biome comprises marshes that are transitional intertidals between land and salty or brackish marine water (e.g.: sloughs, bays, estuaries). It is dominated by halophytic (salt tolerant) herbaceous plants. The daily tidal surges bring in nutrients, which tend to settle in roots of the plants within the salt marsh. The natural chemical activity of salty (or brackish) water and the tendency of algae to bloom in the shallow unshaded water also allow for great biodiversity.

name: marine sponge reef biome
synonyms: sponge reef, sponge reefs, Hexactinellid sponges
definition: The marine sponge reef biome comprises marine reefs primarily built by marine sponges. The primary frame-building sponges are all members of the order Hexactinosa. They are found only in glacier-scoured troughs of low-angle continental shelf. The seafloor is stable and consists of rock, coarse gravel, and large boulders.

name: marine subtidal rocky reef biome
synonyms: rocky reef, rocky reefs, subtidal reef, subtidal reefs
definition: The marine rocky subtidal reef biome comprises regions of the marine reef biome composed mainly of rock and which harbour abundant communities of algae and invertebrates. These reefs are often very patchy, with alterations of rocks dominated by rich invertebrate assemblages and turf-forming calcareous red algae.

name: marine upwelling biome
synonyms: upwelling zone, upwelling ecosystem, ocean upwelling, sea upwelling, marine upwelling
definition: A marine biome which contains communities adapted to living in an environment determined by an upwelling process.

name: marine white smoker biome
synonyms: white smoker, hydrothermal vent, white smokers, deep sea vent, deep sea vents
definition: A marine white smoker biome comprises regions of the marine hydrothermal vent biome characterised by lightly hued plumes, typically containing barium, calcium, and silicon. These vents tend to have lower temperature plumes when compared to black smoker environments.

name: marsh
definition: A wetland ecosystem which includes communities of grasses, rushes, reeds, typhas, sedges, and other herbaceous plants (possibly with low-growing woody plants).

name: meadow ecosystem
synonyms: meadows, meadowland, meadow grass, meadow grassland
definition: A grassland ecosystem which contains a variety of annual, biennial and perennial plants growing on rolling or flat terrain.

name: mediterranean biome
definition: A biome which is subject to mediterranean climatic conditions.

name: mediterranean forest
synonyms: mediterranean forests, mediterranean woodlands, mediterranean scrub, mediterranean scrublands
definition: A forest ecosystem which includes communities adapted to 1) hot to warm, dry summers, 2) mild to cold, rainy winters, and 3) the influence of large, usually marine, bodies of water.

name: mediterranean forest biome
synonyms: mediterranean forests, mediterranean woodlands, mediterranean scrub, mediterranean scrublands
definition: A mediterranean forest in which dominant ecological communities have reached their climax successional state.

name: mediterranean grassland
definition: A grassland which is subject to mediterranean climatic conditions.

name: mediterranean grassland biome
definition: A subtropical grassland biome which includes communities adapted to hot to warm, dry summers, mild to cold, rainy winters, and the influence of large, usually marine, bodies of water.

name: mediterranean savanna biome
definition: A savanna biome which is subject to mediterranean climate patterns.

name: mediterranean sea biome
definition: The mediterranean sea biome comprises mostly enclosed seas that have limited exchange of deep water with outer oceans and where the water circulation is dominated by salinity and temperature differences rather than winds.

name: mediterranean shrubland biome
definition: A mediterranean shrubland biome is a subtropical shrubland biome which includes communities adapted to hot to warm, dry summers, mild to cold, rainy winters, and the influence of large, usually marine, bodies of water.

name: mediterranean woodland biome
definition: A subtropical woodland biome which includes communities adapted to hot to warm, dry summers, mild to cold, rainy winters, and the influence of large, usually marine, bodies of water.

name: migration path
definition: An ecological corridor through which organisms move during a migration process.

name: mixed forest
definition: A forest ecosystem which contains densely packed populations or communities of broadleaf and coniferous trees, strongly limiting light penetration to the forest floor.

name: mixed forest biome
definition: A mixed forest in which dominant ecological communities have reached their climax successional state.

name: mixed grassland
synonyms: mixed grasslands, tall and short grasses, short and tall grasses
definition: A grassland which contains a mixture of tall and short grasses.

name: montane biome
definition: A biome which is subject to montane altitudinal conditions.

name: montane conifer woodland
synonyms: montane conifer ecosystem, montane woodland, montane woodlands
definition: A montane conifer woodland is a conifer woodland which is located within an altitude range that falls between mid-altitude forests and the tree line.

name: montane desert biome
definition: A montane desert biome is a desert biome which occurs in regions elevated above sea level and which has community structure determined by elevation-dependent environmental conditions.

name: montane forest
definition: Montane forests occur between the submontane zone and the subalpine zone

name: montane grassland
definition: High altitude grasslands and shrublands around the world

name: montane grassland biome
definition: A montane grassland biome is a grassland biome which occurs in regions elevated above sea level and which has community structure determined by elevation-dependent environmental conditions.

name: montane savanna biome
definition: A montane savanna biome is a savanna biome which occurs in regions elevated above sea level and which has community structure determined by elevation-dependent environmental conditions.

name: montane shrubland biome
definition: A montane shrubland biome is a shrubland biome which occurs in regions elevated above sea level and which has community structure determined by elevation-dependent environmental conditions.

name: moor
definition: A wetland found in upland areas, characterised by acidic soils.

name: mouth environment
definition: An environment that is determined by a mouth.

name: mudflat
definition: A wetland that forms when mud is deposited by the tides, rivers, sea or oceans.

name: needleleaf forest
definition: Needleleaf forest is composed largely of conifers: straighttrunked, cone-shaped trees with relatively short branches and small, narrow, needle-like leaves.

name: oak woodland
definition: An oak woodland is a woodland which has a tree community primarily composed of oak trees.

name: ocean biome
definition: A marine biome which is determined by an ocean.

name: oceanic abyssopelagic zone biome
definition: The abyssopelagic zone biome comprises the marine water column below the bathypelagic zone biome at approximately 2500 -2700 m and extends either to the hadal pelagic zone biome (at approximately 6000 m) or to the benthopelagic zone biome within ca. 100 m of the seafloor. The depth of 2700 m may be critical for physiological reasons as the change in hydrostatic pressure across this depth may preclude organism migration.

name: oceanic bathypelagic zone biome
synonyms: bathyal zone, bathypelagic, midnight zone, bathypelagic zone
definition: The bathypelagic zone biome comprises the marine water column below approximately 1000 m water depth - the maximum depth to which detectable daylight penetrates in all but the clearest oligotrophic waters - and extends to about 2500 - 2700 m water depth. In the temperate Atlantic, the beginning of the bathypelagic zone biome approximates to the deep oxygen minimum and the base of the permanent thermocline.

name: oceanic benthopelagic zone biome
definition: The benthopelagic zone biome comprises regions of the marine water column which usually coincide with the benthic boundary layer (BBL) - the layer of isothermal and isohaline water contiguous to the sea floor. A general reversal in the declining gradient of pelagic biomass may be observed here, perhaps explained by viable nutrition on the sea floor being resuspended by bottom currents. This zone typically extends 100 m above the seafloor, but may reach upto1000 m during benthic storms.

name: oceanic epipelagic zone biome
synonyms: photic zone, euphotic zone, epipelagic zone, sunlight zone
definition: The oceanic epipelagic zone biome comprises regions of the marine water column that occur offshore, beyond a continental shelf. This biome extends from the surface of the ocean to a depth of ca. 200-250m. Throughout the zone the light field tends to be asymmetrical vertically, so that the direction and elevation of the sun can still be detected. The oceanic epipelagic zone biome encompasses the euphotic zone and, where and when it occurs, the seasonal thermocline.

name: oceanic hadal pelagic zone biome
synonyms: hadal pelagic zone, hadal zone, hadopelagic
definition: The oceanic hadal pelagic zone biome comprises the water column in oceanic trenches occurring at depths between 6000m and 10,000m.

name: oceanic mesopelagic zone biome
definition: The oceanic mesopelagic zone biome comprises regions of the marine water column that occur offshore, beyond a continental shelf. This biome extends through the water column from approximately 200-1000 m depth - the maximal depth of light penetration in all but the clearest oligotrophic ocean regions. In comparison to the epipelagic zone, dominant forms of pelagic organisms do not change very much; however, there are marked changes in species composition and the proportion of smaller-sized individuals decreases.

name: oceanic sea surface microlayer biome
synonyms: sea surface microlayer, sea surface, ocean surface, ocean surface microlayer
definition: The oceanic sea surface microlayer (SML) biome comprises the top 1000 micrometers of the marine surface waters occurring offshore, away from a continental shelf. It is the boundary layer where all exchange occurs between the atmosphere and the ocean. The chemical, physical, and biological properties of the SML differ greatly from the sub-surface water just a few centimeters beneath.

name: oil palm plantation
synonyms: palm oil plantation, oil palm farm, oil palm estate, palm oil farm, palm oil estate
definition: Palm oil is an edible vegetable oil derived from the mesocarp (reddish pulp) of the fruit of the oil palms.

name: olive grove
synonyms: Olea europaea trees, olive farm, olive estate, olive plantation
definition: a small group of Olea europaea trees

name: orchard
definition: An intentional planting of trees or shrubs maintained for food, typically fruit, production.

name: Paramo
definition: An alpine tundra ecosystem which exists above the continuous timberline but below the permanent snowline on elevated land in tropical regions.

name: pasture
definition: A grassland ecosystem which is used for grazing of ungulate livestock as part of a farm or ranch.

name: peatland
definition: A wetland ecosystem which accumulates acidic peat, a deposit of dead plant material.

name: plantation
definition: An intentional planting of a crop, on a large scale, usually for uses other than cereal production or pasture. The term is currently most often used for plantings of trees and shrubs. The term tends also to be used for plantings maintained on economic bases other than that of subsistence farming.

name: planted forest
definition: A forest that has been intentionally established by human intervention.

name: pocasin
definition: A palustrine wetland with deep, acidic, sandy, peat soils. Groundwater saturates the soil except during brief seasonal dry spells and during prolonged droughts. Pocosin soils are nutrient deficient (oligotrophic), especially in phosphorus.

name: polar biome
definition: A biome which is subject to polar climatic conditions.

name: polar desert biome
definition: A polar desert biome is a desert biome which is subject to low levels of insolation, annual precipitation less than 250 millimeters, and a mean temperature less than 10 degrees Celsius during its warmest month. Temperature changes in polar deserts frequently cross the freezing point of water.

name: polar tree-line ecotone
definition: An ecotone which bridges a subpolar coniferous forest biome and a tundra biome.

name: polar tundra ecosystem
definition: A tundra ecosystem which is subject to polar climatic conditions.

name: primary forest
synonyms: old-growth forest, primary forests, virgin forest, late seral forest, primeval forest
definition: Forest which originally covered a region before changes in the environment brought about by people. (Source: PHC)

name: ranch
definition: An area of land used for the herding and grazing of livestock.

name: rangeland biome
synonyms: tallgrass prairies, shortgrass prairies, grazed grasslands
definition: A rangeland biome is an anthropogenic terrestrial biome which is primarily used for the rearing and grazing of livestock.

name: rice field
definition: A paddy field for the cultivation of rice.

name: rubber plantation
synonyms: rubber farm, rubber estate, latex farm, latex estate, latex plantation
definition: Cultivation of natural rubber, or latex, consisting of polymers of the organic compound isoprene, with minor impurities of other organic compounds

name: saline marsh
definition: A marsh whose water contains a considerable quantity of dissolved salts.

name: saline wetland
definition: A wetland ecosystem in which soil is saturated with saline water.

name: savanna biome
definition: A savanna biome is a woodland biome which has seasonal water availability and includes, across its entire spatial extent, trees spaced sufficiently far apart to allow an unbroken layer of grass, sedge (Cyperaceae) or  rush (Juncaceae) communities to live.

name: shrubland biome
definition: A shrubland biome is a terrestrial biome which includes, across its entire spatial extent, dense groups of shrubs.

name: sisal plantation
definition: A species of flowering plant native to southern Mexico but widely cultivated and naturalized in many other countries that yields a stiff fibre used in making rope and various other products.

name: skin environment
synonyms: lives on skin, lives in skin
definition: An environment determined by an area or zone of skin tissue.

name: small freshwater lake biome
synonyms: small fresh water lake, small freshwater lake, small freshwater lakes
definition: A biome which is determined by a small freshwater lake.

name: small river biome
synonyms: small river, small rivers, river, rivers
definition: A small water body which drains a land mass, carrying water down from higher areas to a lower point, oftentimes ending in another body of water.

name: subalpine biome
definition: A biome which is subject to subapline altitudinal conditions.

name: subpolar biome
definition: A biome which is subject to subpolar climatic conditions.

name: subtropical biome
definition: A biome which is subject to subtropical climatic conditions.

name: sugar plantation
synonyms: sugar farm, sugar estate, sugarcane farm, sugarcane estate
definition: A commercial agricultural facility found in tropical climates where sugarcane is grown.

name: swamp ecosystem
definition: A wetland ecosystem in which land mass is permanently inundated by shallow bodies of water, generally with a substantial number of hummocks, or dry-land protrusions.

name: tea plantation
definition: A commercial agricultural facility found in tropical climates where sugarcane is grown.

name: temperate biome
definition: A biome which is subject to temperate climatic conditions.

name: temperate desert biome
definition: A temperate desert biome is a desert biome which has communities adapted to intermediate insolation, low rainfall, and large temperature variations between winter and summer. Winter temperatures may fall below 0 degrees Celsius. Some precipitation in this biome may fall as snow.

name: temperate forest
definition: A forest ecosystem which is subject to temperate climate conditions.

name: temperate grassland
synonyms: temperate grasslands, prairie, pampas, veld, steppe
definition: The predominant vegetation in this biome consists of grass and/or shrubs. The climate is temperate and ranges from semi-arid to semi-humid.

name: temperate grassland biome
synonyms: temperate grasslands, prairie, pampas, veld, steppe
definition: The predominant vegetation in this biome consists of grass and/or shrubs. The climate is temperate and ranges from semi-arid to semi-humid.

synonyms: temperate shrublands, prairie, pampas, veld, steppe

name: terrestrial biome
synonyms: lives in soil, lives on land
definition: A biome which is  primarily or completely situated on a landmass.

name: terrestrial ecoregion
synonyms: lives in soil, lives on land
definition: An ecoregion which is located on a landmass.

name: terrestrial ecosystem
synonyms: lives in soil, lives on land
definition: An ecosystem which is located on a landmass.

name: tidal mudflat
synonyms: tidal mudflats, tidal mud flats, tidal muddy wetlands
definition: A level tract lying at a small depth below the surface of water, or alternately covered and left bare by the tide.

name: tree line ecotone
definition: An ecotone which overlaps at least one biome which supports the growth and persistence of trees and at least one that does not. Before ceasing altogether, tree growth becomes sparse and trees appear stunted as conditions become less favourable along this ecotone.

name: tropical biome
definition: A biome which is subject to tropical climatic conditions.

name: tropical desert biome
definition: A tropical desert biome is a desert biome which has communities adapted to temperatures above a monthly average of 18 degrees Celsius, high daily temperature ranges of approximately 20 degrees Celsius, very high insolation due to inhibited cloud formation, and very low precipitation. Tropical desert biomes located near coasts with cold upwellings may have cooler temperatures and reduced insolution due to fog.

name: tropical forest
definition: A forest ecosystem which is subject to tropical climate conditions.

name: tropical grassland
definition: A grassland ecosystem which is subject to tropical climatic conditions.

name: tropical grassland biome
definition: A grassland ecosystem which is subject to tropical climatic conditions.

name: tropical savanna biome
definition: A savanna ecosystem which is subject to tropical climatic conditions.

name: tropical shrubland biome
definition: A shrubland ecosystem which is subject to tropical climatic conditions.

name: tropical woodland biome
definition: A woodland ecosystem which is subject to tropical climatic conditions.

name: tundra biome
synonyms: tundra, arctic tundra, alpine tundra, antarctic tundra
definition: A terrestrial biome which comprises a tundra ecosystem that has reached its climax community.

name: tundra ecosystem
synonyms: tundra, arctic tundra, alpine tundra, antarctic tundra
definition: An ecosystem which 1) typically has monthly average temperatures below 10 degrees Celsius 2) has a low evapotranspiration ratio 3) is dominated by treeless terrain, covered by communities of low-growing vegetation such as dwarf shrubs, sedges and grasses, mosses, and lichens, 4) contains areas of soil underlain by permafrost with a thin active layer and 5) occurs in both polar and alpine regions (i.e., both high latitudes and high altitudes), and 5) does not have permanent snow or ice cover.

name: tundra mire
synonyms: tundra peatlands, tundra bog, tundra wetlands
definition: Peatlands with a shallow peat layer, only about 500 mm thick, dominated by sedges and grasses. They form in permafrost areas, covering around 110,000 to 160,000 km2 in Alaska, Canada, and the former USSR.

name: urban biome
synonyms: urban environment, urban area, built-up area
definition: An urban biome is a dense settlement biome which has been urbanised.

name: village biome
synonyms: village environment, village area, human settlements
definition: A village biome is an anthropogenic terrestrial biome which contains settlements such as villages, towns, and/or small cities and which is primarily used for agricultural activity.

name: vineyard
definition: A place where grapes are grown for making wine, raisins or table grapes.

name: wetland ecosystem
definition: A terrestrial ecosystem which is inundated or saturated by surface or ground water at a frequency and duration sufficient to support, and that under normal circumstances does support, a prevalence of vegetation typically adapted for life in saturated soil conditions.

name: woodland biome
definition: A woodland biome is a terrestrial biome which includes, across its entire spatial extent, woody plants spaced sufficiently far apart to allow light penetration to support communities of herbaceous plants or shrubs living closer to the woodland floor.

name: woodland ecosystem
definition: An ecosystem which is determined by communities of plants with a tree growth form and in which members of those communities are spaced sufficiently far apart to allow sunlight to illuminate the understory.
